<subSubSection id="F62B1812AD8C4983DC7A930115FECF79" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="6120D28FEC9E3C665D0C08C4FA48749F" pageNumber="1">
The Neotropical killifish genus 
<taxonomicName id="79480559CFE0F6F1C0EC63852AF6B3F7" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7737CC47-FB47-4DAF-87C2-18950BAD40FA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus Poey 1860:307" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rivulus Poey</taxonomicName>
is a speciose assemblage with about 100 valid species occurring in most river basins of Middle and South America (Costa, 2003a, 2004a). The greatest diversity of the genus is concentrated in the area comprising river basins draining the Guiana Shield in northern South America, from where numerous species have been described in recent years (e.g., Costa, 2003b, 2004b, c; Huber, 1991, 1992; Lasso et al, 1992; Thomerson et al., 1991a, 1991b, 1992; Vermeulen &amp; 
<normalizedToken id="99EB8882E0514DE23588399A5FAFDB2F" originalValue="Isbrücker">Isbruecker</normalizedToken>
, 2000). Among them, two species of 
<taxonomicName id="1877D1D9277C5C0E920048C0EA618F6A" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7737CC47-FB47-4DAF-87C2-18950BAD40FA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus Poey 1860:307" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rivulus</taxonomicName>
endemic to the Rio Negro basin, Brazilian Amazon, 
<taxonomicName id="D8A04C90BBCFB9CB0A01AC0B53FC3D97" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3F82970E-059D-4190-BBBB-3CEAA8DF4B99" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus romeri Costa 2003:176" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="romeri">R. romeri Costa</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="7B422CBC5EF199639DE5B42FD59B7E4F" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:D9B00C70-6F1F-497B-984A-F96A732C5DD5" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus kirovskyi Costa 2004:10" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kirovskyi">R. kirovskyi Costa</taxonomicName>
, are unique among congeners in having a unique arrangement of supraorbital neuromasts and being the smallest species, reaching about 23 mm SL as adult maximum size (Costa, 2003b, 2004c). A third species of this group, collected in the Rio 
<normalizedToken id="3CEE5BA2930435A9FCF49F1AB3237A50" originalValue="Uatumã">Uatuma</normalizedToken>
basin, is herein described.
</paragraph>
